<module>
    <h>fàg</h>
    <p><g>fàg</g>
        <vb/>
        <en>leave</en></p>

    <section>
        <h>intransitive</h>
        <p><g>fàg</g> can be used as a (pseudo-)intransitive verb expressing ‘departure’ from inside
            a place – <xl>
                <li>
                    <gd>Dh’fhàg a’ chaileag an eaglais.</gd>
                    <tr>The girl left the church.</tr>
                    <ref text=""/>
                </li>
            </xl>
        </p>
        <section id="intr-sbj">
            <h>subjects</h>
            <section>
                <h>people</h>
                <p>Common nouns – <ul>
                        <li><g>fàg <a href="?gd=clann">clann</a> ...</g>
                            <en>children leave ...</en> – <xl>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>’S e an Dùdlachd a bha ann agus bha e fhathast dorcha nuair
                                        a dh’fhàg a’ chlann an taigh.</gd>
                                    <tr>It was December and it was still dark when the children left
                                        the house.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 183</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl></li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>Other examples – <ul>
                        <li>proper nouns – <xl>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>Nach do dh’fhàg Màiri an taigh? Dh’fhàg.</gd>
                                    <tr>Didn’t Mary leave the house? Yes, she did.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 44</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl></li>
                        <li>first person pronouns – <xl>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>Bha an latha fuar agus cha do dh’fhàg sinn an taigh.</gd>
                                    <tr>The day was cold and we didn’t leave the house.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 238</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl>
                        </li>
                        <li>third person pronouns – <xl>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>Bha Màiri agus Seumas anns a’ mhonadh an dé. [...] Dh’ fhàg
                                        iad an taigh tràth anns a’ mhadainn.</gd>
                                    <tr>Mary and James were on the moor yesterday. [...] They left
                                        home early in the morning.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 76</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </section>
        </section>
        <section id="intr-obj">
            <h>objects</h>
            <section>
                <h>buildings</h>
                <p><g>fàg ... <a href="?gd=taigh">taigh</a></g>
                    <en>... leaves a house</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Nach do dh’fhàg Màiri an taigh? Dh’fhàg.</gd>
                            <tr>Didn’t Mary leave the house? Yes, she did.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 44</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Bha Màiri agus Seumas anns a’ mhonadh an dé. [...] Dh’ fhàg iad an
                                taigh tràth anns a’ mhadainn.</gd>
                            <tr>Mary and James were on the moor yesterday. [...] They left home
                                early in the morning.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 76</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Bha an latha fuar agus cha do dh’fhàg sinn an taigh.</gd>
                            <tr>The day was cold and we didn’t leave the house.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 238</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>’S e an Dùdlachd a bha ann agus bha e fhathast dorcha nuair a
                                dh’fhàg a’ chlann an taigh.</gd>
                            <tr>It was December and it was still dark when the children left the
                                house.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 183</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </section>
        </section>
