    <section>
        <h>transitive</h>
        <p><g>fàg</g> can also be used as a (proper) transitive verb expressing ‘abandonment’ of
            something or someone somewhere – <xl>
                <li>
                    <gd>Dh’fhàg a’ chaileag a Bìobull anns an eaglais.</gd>
                    <tr>The girl left her Bible in the church.</tr>
                    <ref text=""/>
                </li>
            </xl>
        </p>
        <section id="trans-sbj">
            <h>subjects</h>
            <section>
                <h>people</h>
                <p>Some examples – <ul>
                        <li>proper nouns – <xl>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>An do dh’fhàg Calum an cù aig an taigh? Dh’fhàg.</gd>
                                    <tr>Did Malcolm leave the dog at the house? Yes, he did.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl>
                        </li>
                        <li>first and second person pronouns – <xl>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>Dh’fhàg mi mo leabhar anns an sgoil.</gd>
                                    <tr>I left my book in the school.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>An do dh’fhàg thu do leabhar anns an sgoil? Cha do dh’fhàg.
                                        Càit an do dh’fhàg thu do leabhar? Dh’fhàg mi mo leabhar air
                                        a bhòrd.</gd>
                                    <tr>Did you leave your book in the school? No, I didn’t. Where
                                        did you leave your book? I left my book on the table.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 48</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </section>
        </section>
        <section id="trans-obj">
            <h>objects</h>
            <section>
                <h>animals</h>
                <p><g>fàg ... <a href="?gd=cuu">cù</a> ...</g>
                    <en>... leaves a dog ...</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>An do dh’fhàg Calum an cù aig an taigh? Dh’fhàg.</gd>
                            <tr>Did Malcolm leave the dog at the house? Yes, he did.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h>artifacts</h>
                <p><g>fàg ... <a href="?gd=leabhar">leabhar</a> ...</g>
                    <en>... leaves a book ...</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Dh’fhàg mi mo leabhar anns an sgoil.</gd>
                            <tr>I left my book in the school.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>An do dh’fhàg thu do leabhar anns an sgoil? Cha do dh’fhàg. Càit an
                                do dh’fhàg thu do leabhar? Dh’fhàg mi mo leabhar air a bhòrd.</gd>
                            <tr>Did you leave your book in the school? No, I didn’t. Where did you
                                leave your book? I left my book on the table.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 48</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </section>
        </section>
        <section id="trans-loc">
            <h>locatives</h>
            <section>
                <h>buildings</h>
                <p><g>fàg ... aig <a href="?gd=taigh">taigh</a> ...</g>
                    <en>... leaves ... at a house</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>An do dh’fhàg Calum an cù aig an taigh? Dh’fhàg.</gd>
                            <tr>Did Malcolm leave the dog at the house? Yes, he did.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
                <p><g>fàg ... ann an <a href="?gd=sgoil">sgoil</a> ...</g>
                    <en>... leaves ... in a school</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Dh’fhàg mi mo leabhar anns an sgoil.</gd>
                            <tr>I left my book in the school.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>An do dh’fhàg thu do leabhar anns an sgoil? Cha do dh’fhàg. Càit an
                                do dh’fhàg thu do leabhar? Dh’fhàg mi mo leabhar air a bhòrd.</gd>
                            <tr>Did you leave your book in the school? No, I didn’t. Where did you
                                leave your book? I left my book on the table.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 48</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h>furniture</h>
                <p><g>fàg ... air <a href="?gd=boord">bòrd</a> ...</g>
                    <en>... leaves ... on a table</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>An do dh’fhàg thu do leabhar anns an sgoil? Cha do dh’fhàg. Càit an
                                do dh’fhàg thu do leabhar? Dh’fhàg mi mo leabhar air a’ bhòrd.</gd>
                            <tr>Did you leave your book in the school? No, I didn’t. Where did you
                                leave your book? I left my book on the table.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 48</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </section>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h>abstract</h>
            <p>The (proper) transitive use of <g>fàg</g> can be extended to express the more
                abstract notion of something or someone being left to remain in some state,
                typically using an adjective – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dh’fhàg a’ chaileag uinneag fosgailte.</gd>
                        <tr>The girl left a window open.</tr>
                        <ref text=""/>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <section id="trans-abstr-sbj">
                <h>subjects</h>
                <section>
                    <h>people</h>
                    <p>Some examples – <ul>
                            <li>proper nouns – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Dh’fhàg Màiri an dorus fosgailte.</gd>
                                        <tr>Mary left the door open.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 237</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </section>
            </section>
            <section id="trans-abstr-obj">
                <h>objects</h>
                <section>
                    <h>things</h>
                    <p><g>fàg ... <a href="?gd=dorus">dorus</a> ...</g>
                        <en>... leaves a door ...</en> – <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Dh’fhàg Màiri an dorus fosgailte.</gd>
                                <tr>Mary left the door open.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 237</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </p>
                </section>
            </section>
            <section id="trans-abs-adj">
                <h>adjectives</h>
                <p><g>fàg ... <a href="?gd=fosgail">fosgailte</a></g>
                    <en>... leaves ... open</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Dh’fhàg Màiri an dorus fosgailte.</gd>
                            <tr>Mary left the door open.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 237</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </section>
        </section>
    </section>

